76561197961150937,Recommended,250560,33281485,Posted: 5 July,all,eau l'Mèr,"If you are into Indie games and like Diablo or similar games,it's definetly worth buying.it's a no brainer as steam sale, but also worth the full price.I have seen some minor negative reviews, who seem to ignore, this game is an indie game.So keep that in mind and don't expect it provide features or graphics like a AAA-game like Diablo 3, etc.Also at the beginning, you should use the filter and only play well rated adventures.The battle system is relatively simple, although the RPG-aspects regarding your character (stats, abilities) are probably as complex as the ones in Diablo 3.You can choose from 4 Classes (Warrior, Rogue, Ice Wizzard, Fire Wizzard), each playable as male or female.although the wizzards feel more like one class. It's basicly the decision in Diablo 2, if you want to play as Fire or Ice sorceress.depending on the equipment you find, you can also play all classes as melee or ranged heroes.- the Warrior is the heavy, resistant melee class- the Rogue is both strong in dealing ranged and melee damage- the Wizzards are strong AoE damage dealers, with the frost wizzard being more able to kite.The fun for someone new is definetly the loot-system, which is nearly as addicting as the loot-system of Diablo 2 or 3.only nearly as addicting, because unfortunately there are not set-items.And of course you leveling up gives you the opportunity to spend skill points on 4 different stats.You basicly play short-storys or whole campaigns, created by other players, so the fun strongly depends on how good the map is, you choose to play.that's why i recommend to use the filter-system, only playing well-rated adventures at first.THE ACTUAL FUN BEGINS, after you have played some standard and user-generated levels,and you start to create your very own adventures using the ACK (adventure creator kit).there you design your own level, building dungeons, villages, forests, etc.placing enemies, NPCs and loot chests in it.and if you use the trigger features, you almost feel a little bit like a game developper yourself, since these triggers are basicly visualized programming functions.Being visualized makes it even for someone, who never has programmed before easy to do basic programming and therefor make your levels more complex.The game also has a multiplayer-feature, making it possible to play every level or campaign as a group.Although due to the relatively small active community, I recommend to play the game with friends, if you want to actually play the multiplayer.But even as a Single-Player, the game is a lot of fun.In a nutshell:it's an Indie-RPG game with a strong editor,worth every penny!"
