,Recommended,250560,29026086,Posted: 4 January,all,Rex Draco,"This is one of those games that is special. It isn't perfect, nor is it amazing, but it's definitely special. The concept is simple, your typical Diablo clone (though it feels more like Gauntlet) with a bit of Little Big Planet.There isn't a whole lot of Little Big Planet influenced content. For example, the way you can customize your character is limited. You find loot and you wear it. The loot makes your character both look different as well boosts some stats, enable some abilities, etc. Little Big Planet wins hard by character customization. As far as level creation goes, it wins as far as I can tell. Maybe it doesn't win by content, for Little Big Planet wins hands down as far as content you can mess with, but this game wins as far as control to the point you can actually make some pretty fun quests.The gameplay is simplistic. You attack, you level up, you develop a play style, you get better, you attack more. You finish levels for loot, coins, and xp. Loot and coins can both be donated to a ""shrine"" in your home level (or pod, if you're thinking little big planet, but you cannot customize it like you could your pod in LBP). When you donate enough and then pray, you then unlock randomly options you can choose from such as a better item, stamina boost, health boost, inventory increase, etc.There is one thing unique beyond all of this, you're doing all of this for one major objective. You are leveling yourself up and grinding for better items so you can fight a dragon. Shocker, a game called Fight the Dragon and it's all about fighting a dragon. The catch is that it has a lot of health, 1 million HP to be exact, and your goal is to fight it and deal as much damage as possible. If you die, the hp doesn'treset. You can die and come back later, continuing where you have left off. This is a cool, interesting, unique game feature.Considering how low of a price this game is, the fact it still has a four pack, and how enjoyable it is, I'd say it's worth full price easily. If you want, you can easily wait for a sale where it goes nearly half off, which is an even more incredible deal. The game might not get 100 hours from me, but I'll get my money's worth."
