,Recommended,250560,24199566,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,Xaliber,"Hack and slash RPG with focus on community-created maps. Fun to play with friends.The strong point on this game I think is the community maps--unlike Torchlight II, you can play the custom maps as soon as you finish the first level. The custom maps are very rich in varieties--ranging from simple hack and slash ""kill the boss"" map, to puzzle and crime investigation and campaign map. The great stuff is the community collaborates together in those custom maps, creating a series of maps with sequencial stories.Here are a few examples of those:http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=559225869http://steamcommunity.com/app/250560/discussions/3/412446292756896658/It's a pretty fun game to play with friends, but it should be noted that the game itself is pretty barebone: albeit having diverse loot (which gives you some different ways of combat), there is no skill tree. You have skill progression but there is no branch. So with only four classes (Fighter, Rogue, Fire Mage, Ice Mage) there aren't much abilities to be invested in. Also, there is no main storyline as the game relies heavily on custom maps.If you want a quick no-brainer hack and slash with very diverse levels and have several friends to play with, go get this game."
,Recommended,250560,9661891,"Posted: 29 March, 2014",all,kit89,"A highly enjoyable game with lots of potential. This review is based on Early Access: Alpha 2.1. The concept of this game is simple, explore an array of user generated dungeons to acquire equipment and improve your character, currently only the Fighter & Fire Lord are available to play.The games combat system is simple and well defined, though I am not entirely comfortable with the controllers interface, I found myself continuosly trying to open( X ) an enemy rather than attack them. Perhaps allow for controller remapping, or provide a map that uses the Left/Right Triggers for combat?Enemy characters look exceptional and are initially enjoyable to slay, however after a few levels I found myself killing the same monsters with little variance in their combat tactics, most monsetrs operate on a run towards player and attack strategy.The game provides a swathe of equipment, with some rather enjoyable names, running through a dungeon can easily see your backpack being full of primarily junk items which you don't seem to be able to sell anywhere. In fact you can accumulate money but I'm not sure where you spend it?Dungeons can feel slightly bland with monsters only being used as the main challenge, hopefully as users become more familiar with the map-editor and the editor provides more tools to create unique set-pieces that provide memorable engagements this will be satiated.Overall I found the game exceptionally enjoyable to play, but as it is Early Access lacking some of the components that could make it a truly great game. I look forward to seeing more from the developer, 3 Sprockets."
