,Not Recommended,250560,35357848,Posted: 30 September,all,Nirrudn,"A neat concept, ruined by a lack of progression.  If you can get this for $2 or less, it's probably worth that.  If you want a massive grind game, this is it.Several hours in to a game with literally thousands of maps to play, and I find myself bored.  The scenery changes but the core gameplay hasn't.  The speed of leveling feels like the original EverQuest.  Two days of playing and I'm level 6 of 60.  I've unlocked one new ability, and I'm otherwise indistinguishable from a brand new character.  I feel like I've made no progress at all with my time investment.It's not even necessarly character progression that's the problem either, it's a lack of depth.  The 4 classes play almost identically. They're so homogeneous they even start with the same equipment as opposed to some class-specific gear.  Equip your weapon of choice and either get in melee range to spam the same button, or stay at range and spam the same button.  It's too monotonous.  The only depth comes in the form of class specific skills, but depending on the map you may not get to use those much at all if the creator neglects to include potions.  This plays like a mobile game, not a desktop one.If you're looking for a 10-point rating, I'd say this is a 5."
76561197995158485,Recommended,250560,21273438,"Posted: 17 February, 2016",all,Searanox,"I give a very HESITANT Thumb-up. I'll explain.I can't really judge this as a game, as much as I have to judge it as a toolbox. And, as with any game where you hand the keys to the kingdom to the playerbase, only about 1 in 12 actually knows what they're doing. :(In Fight the Dragon you're given a battle arena against a red dragon with 1 MILLION health, and told to go questing from map to map to build yourself up and fight him. Any damage the dragon takes is cumulative, so even the 2 points of damage you do to him at lvl1 will stay.So, you leap from player-made map to player-made map, fighting monsters and finding loot. As I said, most folks should not be given the tools to make game levels, as they don't know what is appealing, what flows well or even what looks good. I found myself with serious respect for the real industry after playing 50+ maps (there's an achievement for that), and only really liking about 8 of them.But back to the dragon. Each time you finish a level you get a dragon ticket/scroll, which gives you three lives to fight the dragon in the special arena. As I said your damage sticks, so you run in and do as much damage as you can before he freaking annihilates you. Most battles last about 30 seconds, even with three lives. So you chip away at him over time as you level up Just remember:-Fire Resist does NOT work on the Dragon-You CANNOT bring your magic rings, arguably the best items in the game.-Almost all the dragon's attacks have major push-back, so good luck if you're a melee characterThe dragon fight is VERY unfair, and if that is the focus of your time in this game you're going to have a bad time. Instead, I spent my questing hours in search of a good map that felt like a real video game level, and not just something a 9 year-old threw together to mess with people. Not all levels are created equal, and it comes with a thumbs up/sideways/down function, and the ability to leave a comment on the level itself. I blasted a LOT of bad levels, trust me, and praised a few good ones.Fight the Dragon is a cute rpg toolbox, but if you judge by the player-made content, not an especially good game. Get it on sale for a quick distraction, but this is not something to devote to.TL:DR Version:-Dragon has 1 Million HP, you chip away at his health over many attempts.-Dragon fight does not respect fire resistance, magic rings, and allows you no health/mana items.-Dragon can kill you three times in under 40 seconds, burning your Dragon Fight attempt currency.-All the levels outside the tutorial are player-made, most of them are really bad.-Cute, addictive, but not something you're ever going to finish. Only the INSANE will grind away the hours to ACTUALLY slay the dragon."
