76561197972155384,Recommended,250560,14154171,"Posted: 24 January, 2015",all,Caden Elbowslash,"It's a pretty simple hack and slash RPG. Choose a class (amongst the four classes), name the character, voila you're ready to start. I like the unique concept of the gold shrine. You can either donate equipments to the loot shrine (essentially selling them) and getting gold in return. As your gold amont increases, the rank of loot increases giving you superior ranked (not necessarily great depending on what you are building your character towards), stat point, health (don't underestimate this, it's an extremely important perk like in any RPG game), bag slot, and so on. Not to mention if you always wanted to create your own custom map for games, this game provides that very feature. I have been having a blast at the start but the gameplay gets pretty dull after for awhile because the game starts heading towards the usual grinding and farming for gold coins to sell and donate respectively to the loot shrine and get equipments and perks from it.What would be nice to see in future updates are new features such as more specialised classes (like monk, ranger/archer/battle mage, etc) more variety of weapon classes (like bows, knuckles/dusters, fighting staff, etc), more unique features like the ones implemented (loot shrine custom maps, and etc), and if possible a skill tree for all characters so that we can choose what skills we would want therefore allowing us to create a style suited to individuals instead of the fixed 4 skills."
