76561198116786626,Recommended,250560,10108778,"Posted: 14 May, 2014",all,Digital Dragoon,This game is evolving to become a good game. The objective is simple and there is a lot of creative depth. Build levels for users. Explore other users levels. Then battle the dragon.This game is heavily based on user generated levels. There is a lot of depth to creating your own levels and creating a storyline using NPCs.The in game level designer works well and is fun to use. They are currently evolving this part of the game.The objective is to level up your character experience by trying out different levels created by other users. This gives you access to fight the dragon. Then you take as much HP of the dragon on each visit. When you finally deplete the dragon of all its HP you have completed the main quest. The dragon has a huge amount of HP so you will have to play a lot of levels to gain access to the dragon. As you play the levels your character become more experienced making him stronger and more effective against the dragon on the next visit.The graphical interface looks sharp and tidy. The actual game graphics may look simple but are very effective for this type of game. There is not many sound effects in the game but what there is sounds very good. I believe more will be added as the game evolves.Highly recommend this game. Fun and creative to play. The developers are adding and updating this game frequently. The game is missing a couple of things from the date this review was submitted. But it is playable and there is plenty to do.
