,Recommended,250560,21306770,"Posted: 18 February, 2016",all,Chinspinner,"I give this a thumbs up, but only because it is priced at about the right level for the content you can expect.In terms of gameplay, you work your way through hack and slash isometric maps, collect gear and loot, which you either equip or exchange for stat gains or better gear. Completing maps earns you tickets to ""Fight The Dragon"".The maps usually involve a lot of clicking and running, as well as puzzles revolving largely around pressure pads and levers hidden within maze-like environments. Fighting the dragon is simply an arena against a boss.This is reasonably fun for a short period of time, but it has little longevity.The best part of the game is the creator, where you can design and build your own maps and campaigns. Despite the limiting graphics, there is actually a lot of freedom to build from the ground up, create relatively complex puzzles and interesting environments. Unfortunately, as always with these games, the maps you produce tend to get lost amongst a lot of crap, or go unnoticed beside those few early maps that received ""thumbs ups"" so show up in most people's searches.I give this a tentative recommendation. It is fun but has little longevity."
