,Recommended,250560,10964940,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,Timba3olf,"If all you could think about while slaying your way through Diablo, Dark Alliance or Torchlight was, ""I wish there was a game that let me make my own dungeons and adventures,"" then this is the game for you.Well, sort of. Fight the Dragon is made for dungeons that take less than a half hour to complete, and the terrain and dungeon-building tools are very Lego or Minecraft-esque. They're still smoothing out the combat (which takes more cues from Gauntlet than modern ARPGs), adding more tilesets and enemies, and developing more classes. But it's a thoroughly pleasant experience for an Early Access game. The dungeon-building is intuitive and well-developed, even at this stage. Updates and regular and substansial, and the developers respond to player feedback. Highly reccomended, especially if, like me, you enjoyed the park builder in Tony Hawk's Pro Skater or the dungeon builder in Neverwinter more than the actual game."
