76561198114957721,Not Recommended,250560,19103571,"Posted: 15 November, 2015",all,Captain x Bear,"Firstly I would like to just say that I got this game while it was on sale in a 4-pack for a total of $15-20. I believe this is a very good game and the fact is that the game is good. However, I do not recommend anyone buy this game if they are looking for games similar to what I've been looking for. To elaborate, I am looking forsomething medieval-like,something rpg-likewith dungeons and new loot to find,something challengingand fun at the same time, andmost importantlyit has to bemultiplayer co-opfor at least 4 people. In the months I've randomly searched when I decide to delve into the steam market I've found many games that seem almost perfect but don't have multiplayer or are too expensive for the time being.I am going to prove to you that there arebetter gamesthan this that you can get that have these elements and some are even cheaper. Read on and I will explain....This game is fun at first but the problem is the fact that it is based on you and your friends taking on random dungeons created by players. I marvel at this idea; it is brilliant. The issue is the fact that they are in factplayers, that causing the obvious problem that not every dungeon is good. I am not exaggerating when I say that some dungeons I and my friends have went on are just garbage. I've spent more than 20 minutes on a dungeon with a friend when it should've taken about 5 minutes to complete. You might be thinking ""Oh, that just makes it more challenging"" and you'd be right, it took a long time to simply figure out that while on the inside of some castle wall (I know what you're thinking ""Oh! Castle wall!!! That's so cool"", this was anything but an actual castle.) we had to climb a ladder that was against the inside of the wall which happened to have a small house (not a shack, A HOUSE) which when you go inside seems to have nothing. Then you find out you have to go in a cellar there which we didn't discover existed till after killing everything on the ""dungeon"" (it was more of an outside area) and the only major difficulty was figuring out what to do. Mind you that this was not meant to be a puzzle, it was just bad mapmaking. You were presented with the area for this house right after you kill the things around you when you spawn. The point being is, if you expect anything as great as in the trailer video, I have not found it or even experienced anything that great. I will admit the game is fun, but what I'm trying to prove to you is that there areBETTER ALTERNATIVESto this game if you are looking for similar things as me.Better games for you and a group of friends to try that I've played or intend to play in the future:Trove:It's on steam, it's free, it's a 3rd person MMORPG with a bunch of fun classes like swordsman, archer, ice mage, pirate. There isn't PVP it's PVE oriented, and it has a ""minecraft-esque"" atmosphere. It is a voxel game which I'm normally not into but it's pretty good. Also, despite it being an MMO it does require aiming and you can dodge attacks if you jump and such, it is not lock on and just press a button to kill things like a lot of MMO's. Whenever you and your friends are near each other you all get xp despite whomever kills a creature and you all get your own specific loot drops that only you see, when you open up chests, that are based on your class. So there are no arguments over splitting up loot, you get the same amount of loot and xp with a group as solo-ing. So it's better with friends, you level up faster that way. There also are bosses at the end of dungeons.To sum it up: As my friends and I describe it, it is basically Fight The Dragon But Better.Sky Saga:Currently in alpha and free. It is not on steam and does require a key that you get when you sign up for an account on their webpage and email you a key. It is an MMORPG and very, very. similar to Minecraft in virtually every way except it's less about the building and more focused on getting quests by talking to npc's at the hub and you go on adventures. You might have to get an item you've never gotten before and bring it back to the hub, or just go take on dungeons and they do have somewhat difficult bosses in dungeons. I was co-oping a dungeon with a friend and they left for some reason and I was stuck with half health and found a boss and basically just ran out of the dungeon cause I couldn't take him. It was this big dude who had a giant lance or something and would swing it at me.To sum it up: I don't know when they will be releasing keys again as of this moment though, butdefinitely checkthis out and make an account if you're interested in playing in the future.Also be sure to check your ""promotions"" tab in gmail if that's what you use, it got sent there for me.Secrets of Grindea:This game I have not played or own yet. But from what I gather it is multiplayer with up to 4 players and basically a top-down RPG with monsters and boss fights. I don't know what else there is but it appears to have the elements I'm looking for in dugeon style games. It is currently $15 the same price as fight the dragon. So if you don't want to at least try the free games I mentioned and you do want to spend money still. This game is most definitely an option.To sum it up: Same price as Fight The Dragon but probably better.In Conclusion:Look up any and all of these Games and if you are truly looking for the same elements I sought after, you will not be disappointed. And if you are, you will be even more disappointed by buying Fight The Dragon. I release this review to help people like me get the best game possible for them and their friends. Good luck all and have a great day! After all you are on Steam! :)"
