76561198036142978,Recommended,250560,14816610,"Posted: 9 March, 2015",all,Bonticune,"This game is fun. The map editing program is extensive and I spent a while making some complicated maps. The game is very basic, you gain levels by playing either creator made maps, your maps or maps of other users and eventually defeat the dragon.Pros:Map making is easy and fun, and you can accomplish a good amount in a short time.The gameplay is pretty fluid, although sometimes when you try to hit an enemy with a sword nothing happens. That could just be a miss on the attack, but it isn't indicated.The loot system reminds me of Borderlands.The dragon is VERY tough to beat. After pouring several hours into leveling up and getting good gear to fight the dragon I've still only been able to knock out a few thousand health from it per battle. It starts out with a million health, but health doesn't regenerate in between battles, so the damage you do to it is permanent. If you get health regenerating equipment and are willing to run around the map for about 48 hours to avoid attacks while you heal, then you could beat the dragon in one sitting, but I do not recommend you try.Cons:Once a moderator accuses your map of being an exploit, it seems they never go back to unban it after you edit it. For example, I built a map that was a straight shot from beginning to end with a couple hundred rats and skeletons to fight. It was by no means an easy map. I would usually beat it with just a single life left. Because of Its simplicity it was banned for being a grinding exploit, and now that I edited it to include Minotaurs (which easily knock a player off my map, thereby increasing the difficulty greatly) It's still in review.Although bugs are fixed quickly and little things are added here and there, no real new content has shown up to my knowledge since my purchase of the game a few months ago. The game's replay value sinks quickly after you unlock your final ability and realize the only thing you have left to do is suffer through endless generic hours of gameplay to get a bit stronger to stand up to the dragon better.You can't just go and challenge the dragon whenever you want. You need a scroll, and to get it you need to play a new map. If you don't have an internet connection, you will run out of scrolls quickly and won't be able to play the main purpose of the game.Overall, the game is good, and I recommend it if you're willing to do the same thing for a while in order ot beat that pesky dragon, and if you're willing to put up with moderators banning you for exploiting, then not giving you a second chance. Don't mess up in map editing, or you'll end up like me, the evil Bonticune.Things I'd like to see:A multiplayer option to fight the dragon with. Maybe a dragon whose health resets after each battle, and some prize system if you do a certain amount of damage.Different equipment when you deal enough damage to the dragon. The time limit rings are good for the few minutes you get them, but the rings that last for even as high as an hour and a half are gone a lot quicker than people would think.A difficulty higher than extreme. I like heavy combat in my games, and with health regen equipment the game has become too easy.The ability to have bosses speak before they attack.The field of views for enemies increased (if the player makes it so while editing)"
