,Recommended,250560,17842265,"Posted: 1 September, 2015",all,THE KRAKEN,"We have Fight The Dragon; an indie RPG from 3 Sprockets. Let’s get rocking.The GoodFtD has an impressively high replay value. The game itself consists of thousands of 10 – 15 minute (on average) adventures for your character to go on. This keeps things interesting and ensures that you don’t get stuck in a quagmire of monotony.FtD includes an editor which allows you to build your own adventures and maps and not only play them, but share them with the rest of the community. (Steam Workshop is a big plus to any game in my opinion.)This game is rather addictive. You get into the “just one more” mentality and find yourself still slapping skeletons with bladed instruments hours later.The graphics have their own charming quality to them and it is fun to see different maps on every adventure.The BadOnce or twice I’ve had my character glitch out and rocket across the screen which resulted in my death. Not cool.The camera angle isn’t always the best thing for you.The game is kind of dark no matter what your gamma is set to.The MehAs far as character customization goes, FtD has a limited amount to offer you. While there is Steam Workshop, there’s still not much too it.Weapon and armor varieties are also limited and the same goes for enemy variety.Verdict: YeaIf you’re looking for a solid time killer and/or something you can get together with your friends and play to have a great time, look no further. You can pick up Fight The Dragon here on Steam or you can watch the Humble Bundle End of Summer Sale and try your luck there. As always, thanks for reading."
