,Not Recommended,250560,17895574,"Posted: 5 September, 2015",all,melissahk,"I played Fight the Dragon last night with a friend, and I don't really have any desire to play it again. I love dungeon crawlers (huge fan of the Diablos and Torchlights). I found this game to be quite glitchy (random locking of items, spell/ability book on the side of the house not available, not being able to switch inputs even after re-loading the game), and so did my friend. We didn't play the campaign, we just went for reward runs, and while most of the levels were great in concept, the designs in terms of gameplay were at times frustrating (like being able to get to a water area past a cliff but no way to get back, or killing a boss that opens a door on a timer, not making it in time, and the only option was to quit the level rather than try again). I got the humour of things like the item names and the NPC dialogues, but I found that it grew tiresome after a few hours. Maybe if there wasn't the frustration of the glitches, that might not have been the case.I really like the concept, and I certainly see why it was supported. But in actual gameplay, it just didn't speak to me personally. Based on the reviews, it obviously spoke to others, though. :-)"
