76561197998214072,Recommended,250560,34069905,Posted: 6 August,all,MrXFactor,"This is a kind of game we could really use more of. Gameplay is fun and engaging, leveling up feels rewarding, and the fact that the game relies on levels made by the community rather than its own really saves on space usage. My only gripe is the blocking system. Your shield has its own health bar which deteriorates way faster than it should. It's a tad annoying, especially when you're in a room full of archers.ACK is probably one of the best editors I've used for a game so far. It's so easy to use, but the possibilities of what you can make with it are staggering. My only complaint about it is that when it comes to placing monsters in your map, you don't really have that many options with them. You can only name them, make them slightly stronger or slightly weaker, change their appearance and link them to triggers. A shame because I had a horror map in mind and I needed a monster that was unkillable.All in all, Fight the Dragon is awesome! Very much worth the asking price of 15 bucks. And just a little warning for the newcomers out there. Watch out for the skeleton archers. I've got level 5 characters and they're STILL my biggest problem."
